From 1e9fe74c14d28f8b4b7e1b6410be2d3eaf5af795 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Aaradhana Sahu <aaradhana.sahu@oss.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Sep 2025 15:56:22 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:CP:wifi:mac80211: Fix crash due to stale
 sta->deflink.pub pointer during link removal

During link removal, when the deflink is replaced with another link,
the host copies only link_sta_info and ieee80211_link_sta into
sta->deflink and sta->sta.deflink. Since these structures are
dynamically allocated in ieee80211_sta_allocate_link(), and
link_sta_info->ieee80211_link_sta points to dynamic memory, the
sta->deflink.pub ends up referencing a stale pointer after the
original allocation is freed in sta_remove_link().

Fix this by correctly assigning sta->deflink.pub to the valid
sta->sta.deflink to avoid the crash.

Patch-dependency:
0237-wifi-mac80211-Handle-link-sta-removal-during-ML-reco.patch
Patch-work: None

Signed-off-by: Aaradhana Sahu <aaradhana.sahu@oss.qualcomm.com>
---
 net/mac80211/sta_info.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/net/mac80211/sta_info.c b/net/mac80211/sta_info.c
index 64e981a..c838360 100644
--- a/net/mac80211/sta_info.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/sta_info.c
@@ -3452,6 +3452,7 @@ void ieee80211_sta_remove_link(struct sta_info *sta, unsigned int link_id,
 
 			memcpy(&sta->deflink, sta_info, sizeof(*sta_info));
 			memcpy(&sta->sta.deflink, link_sta, sizeof(*link_sta));
+			sta->deflink.pub = &sta->sta.deflink;
 
 			/* Free the moved link memory */
 			sta_remove_link(sta, n_link_id, true);
-- 
